Q: A rectangular piece of 150 sq m has a length which is 1m more than the 4 times the breadth. What is the perimeter of the piece?
Options: (a) 60 m (b) 61 m (c) 62 m (d) 63 m (e) 64 m
A:
Perimeter of a rectangular piece = 2(l + b) where l is the length and b is the breadth. Since the length is 1m more than 4 times the breadth, l = 4b + 1. Now, the area of the piece is 150 sq m. So, we can set up the equation: 2(4b + 1 + 2b) = 150. Simplifying, we get: 2b + 2 = 75. b = 37.5. So, the perimeter of the piece is 2(4b + 1 + 2b) = 2(4(37.5) + 1 + 2(37.5)) = 62 m. The answer is (c).

