Q: Everyone in the family earns money each month. If the total income of a family per month is $9000 and the median income is $3000, how many members are there in the family?
Options: (a) 2 (b) 3 (c) 4 (d) 5 (e) 6
A:
The median income of the family is $3000, which means that half of the income goes to the lower half of the family. So the income of the lower half is $3000 * 2 = $6000. The total income of the family is $9000, so the income of the upper half is $9000 - $6000 = $3000. The number of members in the family is half of the income of the lower half, which is half of $6000 = $3000 / 2 = $1500. So the answer is (c).

