Q: Three bells ring at intervals of 36 seconds, 40 seconds and 48 seconds, respectively. They start ringing together at a particular time. When they will ring together again?
Options: (a) After 6 minutes (b) After 12 minutes (c) After 18 minutes (d) After 24 minutes (e) none
A:
Let the time they start ringing together be T. Then, the time they will ring together again is T + (36 + 40 + 48) = T + 156 = 156 + T. T = 156/3 = 52 minutes. So the answer is (a).

